# This class introduced the fundamentals of computer networking, including network structure, models, protocols, and security.

# We learned about network architecture, the OSI model, the TCP/IP protocol stack, sockets, HTTP, FTP, SMTP, DNS, P2P, TCP, UDP, reliable data transfer, flow control, congestion control, IP addressing, routing, forwarding, error detection, Ethernet, ARP, switching, wireless standards, network threats, and security countermeasures.
